.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- basic UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that executes commands.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
\fBInteractive mode\fR
Displays prompt and waits for input
.TP
\fBNon-interactive mode\fR
Reads commands from pipe or file
.TP
\fBBuilt-in commands\fR
exit, env

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit [status]
Exit shell with optional status
.TP
.B env
Print environment variables

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive:
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) ls
main.c shell.h
($) exit
.fi

Non-interactive:
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.h
.fi

.SH RETURN VALUE
Exit status of last command

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2)

.SH AUTHORS
Shaden Khaled, Owen Algarni
